# Target: `block_select_topk` -- the MiniMax-M3 sparse-attention (MSA) indexer's
# block-selection core (shared by the prefill + decode indexer phases). A test
# launcher runs one CTA per score row; we fuzz the shape (num_rows, num_blocks,
# k), the launch width (block_dim), and the score distribution. Two oracles: a
# VALIDITY CONTRACT (always on: in-range / distinct / -1-tail / no-winner -> all
# -1, on a fresh -2-poisoned int32 output + an OOB scores guard) and `ref`
# (--check: the top-k correctness invariant). Hardware-independent (no SM100),
# so it runs on any non-Apple GPU.
mojo_test(
    name = "fuzz_sparse_indexer.mojo.test",
    size = "large",
    srcs = [
        "_fuzz.mojo",
        "fuzz_sparse_indexer.mojo",
